<sect1 id="analysis_class_page_1analysis_internal">
<title>Internal Architecture</title>
<sect2 id="analysis_class_page_1analysis_workflow">
<title>Internal Workflow</title>
<para>When <computeroutput>start()</computeroutput> is called, the following private methods execute:</para>
<para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para><bold>check_cache()</bold>: Look for cached data to skip reprocessing</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>build_project()</bold>: Create output directory structure</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>build_events()</bold>: Process raw data into event objects</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>build_selections()</bold>: Apply selection criteria</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>build_graphs()</bold>: Convert events to graph representations</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>build_dataloader()</bold>: Prepare data for training</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>build_model_session()</bold>: Configure model training sessions</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>build_inference()</bold>: Set up inference pipeline (if applicable)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>build_metric()</bold>: Calculate performance metrics</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="analysis_class_page_1analysis_threading">
<title>Threading Model</title>
<para>The analysis uses a multi-threaded approach:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Event processing runs in parallel across files</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="classGraph" kindref="compound">Graph</ref> construction is parallelized per event</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Model training uses batched parallel operations</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Metric calculation can run concurrently with training</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect2>
</sect1>
